@Brandon-Tai, the best performing TensorFlow models tend to feed the examples into a queue with a different Python thread, or use one of the reader op to read in the examples, instead through feed_dict.

https://www.tensorflow.org/versions/r0.10/api_docs/python/io_ops.html#readers

We can take a look a this model and see if there are other issues beside feed_dict.
